text:
Dine here mainly because of the zhi char stall (large serving and tasty food), western stall (enexpectedly very good), stall selling superb satay and mamak stall (rojak n goreng 2 stuff satisfaction guarantee).

The place has a chillex atmosphere. Not crowded.

Well had to try Diana's Kitchen prawn noodles......they were pretty good with good portion served.....had the crayfish noodle....did not disappointüëçüëçüëç The chicken rice from the shop beside is good too
Other than a bit salty, everything is good especially they use real slice fish unlike others using process fish slices.
Tried the food from all the shops there. Very bad taste. Hope they can do better. It was much much better last time.
Food taste is good and there's a wide variety of choices of local dishes and old-school kueh. I will return for more.
